rial taxa that share hosts and transmission mechanism hinting towards hitherto unknown features on pathogen ecology, e.g.\n              Salmonella\n              versus\n              Campylobacter\n              and\n              Anaplasma\n              versus\n              Borrelia\n              . Our results suggest that rising temperature and increasing precipitation will accelerate the threat of bird\u2010 and bat\u2010associated bacterial and viral pathogens to wildlife, domesticated animals and humans, respectively. However, the idiosyncratic relationships with climatic conditions among pathogenic taxa highlight the need for pathogen\u2010specific predictive models to understand future pathogen distributions.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Xu, Yanjie", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Poosakkannu, Anbu", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Suominen, Kati M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Laine, Veronika N.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lilley, Thomas M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pulliainen, Arto T.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Lehikoinen, Aleksi", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Biodiversity", "Mammalia", "Chiroptera", "Chordata", "Animalia", "bats", "bat"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/07931e885d654898e39b76e3de3cabe0", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/a09d67bc32c0ef0367150b2dfc9583b23f16213dd29b79d0a8f08b4ae95fb066", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/5435545/items/4EI6PGIQ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/5435545/items/4EI6PGIQ", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/c25d8171ea0cf2adb5b01bd4fb19ad6c!/b329600-332058", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/330417efcaa2560c9b8ebcd6fae17ce0", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.